The paper deals with image analysis and classification using machine learning techniques, which suggests that it belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of dictionary learning and sparsity constraints also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also deals with histopathological images, which suggests that it could belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the use of real-world image databases and the mention of brain tumor images suggests that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
